{
  "text": "This implies that Eve's attack is impossible in principle. What can we do for an entangled input state? Though a direct proof could be impossible, there is an evidence for the statement, the Eq. (5). The Theorem III.3 in [CITATION_1] states that, for a positive operator-valued measure (POVM) {L i } which is implemented using local operation and classical communication (LOCC), i p i \u2212 q i 1 \u2264 \u03b5, where Bob cannot obtain any information for \u03d5 A without Charlie-Alice's key information. Symmetrically Alice's attack is useless. In other words, the Charlie's aim of sharing a quantum state \u03d5 AB between Alice and Bob will be securely accomplished.",
